9.27	The Municipal Ecological Solid Waste Management Coordinator commented that they transferred to the present MRF due to closure of the old one because of issue in lot ownership. As of now, Econest is temporarily closed due to some violations so the component barangays served as storage of wastes for the meantime until the Econest becomes operational again. On the other hand, the Municipality cannot afford yet the cost of garbage truck so they temporarily used the rescue vehicles to maximize the use thereof. With regards to open burning of wastes, they are planning to conduct information education campaign in schools and barangays starting March 2020.

We recommended and management agreed to:

(a)	require the OIC – MT to (i) monitor the activities of all collecting officers, designated tellers and collectors under his jurisdiction;



(ii) enforce prompt and complete remittance of collections, including cash tickets, in the custody of cash accountable officers;



(iii) ensure compliance by the AF custodian on the proper inventory recording and reporting of accountable forms; and 



(iv) instruct collectors to support remittance of collections with properly accomplished/signed RCD and report on the accountability for AFs;

(b)	guard against collecting officers who retain significant amount of collections and require them to remit the same to the Municipal Treasurer before leaving the premises of the Office of the Municipal Treasurer; and

(c)	issue the AFs in numerical sequence to institute better control and facilitate detection of missing ones.

We recommended and management agreed to:

(a)	instruct the Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator (MPDC) to plan carefully the projects to be included under the Local Government Development Program Priority Projects for Funding which embodies PPAs to be specifically funded by the 20% Development Fund, and the concerned officials to coordinate closely so that the needs of every end – user are properly addressed;

(b)	advise the BAC to be more proactive in complying with its duties set forth under the 2016 RIRR of R.A. No. 9184;



(c)	require the Municipal Accountant to exercise diligence in the processing of contractor’s claims to ensure complete and appropriate documentation thereof; and

(d)	require the BAC and the Municipal Accountant to submit the complete set of documents mentioned above.

