We recommended that management:

formally instruct the Municipal Accountant to maintain separate records of subsidiary ledgers for each fund transferred to and received by the Municipality from NGAs and GOCCs, obtain copies of ORs, DVs, Notices of Authority to Debit Account Issued relative to all fund transfers, and recognize the existing two carabaos in the books of accounts;
cancel the existing ARE with respect to the two carabaos and prepare the appropriate Work, Other Animals and Breeding Stocks Ledger Card (WOABSLC);
inform the Municipal Treasurer in writing of the need to maintain separate bank accounts and cashbooks for every fund transfer it received from NGAs, private individuals/groups, and non–government organization;
request for the issuance of a Sangguniang Bayan Resolution allowing the Municipal Treasurer to open a separate bank account for the unexpended balance of the 5% LDRRMF and other trust funds;

submit all the bidding documents, disbursement vouchers and other attendant documents with respect to the aforementioned fund transfers; and

advice the BAC to observe the pertinent provisions of the 2016 RIRR of R.A. No. 9184 in the procurement of government PPAs.

We recommended and management agreed to:

institute stricter control over the processing and releasing of payments of claims to ensure completeness of supporting documents and prompt and immediate rendition of monthly accounts;
submit the accounts and reports for various months and adhere strictly to the timeframes on the submission of accounts and financial reports to the Audit Team pursuant to Section 100 of P.D. No. 1445, and COA Circular No. 2009-006; and (c) see to it that all unsubmitted accounts (vouchers and official receipts) for CY 2016 are transmitted to the Office of the Auditor; otherwise, we shall be constrained to recommend the withholding of salaries of concerned Municipal officials/person-nel.

